{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, the black-box nature of deep learning models allows for improving security.The deep learning-based watermarking scheme is decomposed into three main stages as shown in Fig. 5.",
    "The first stage is the encoder which embeds the signature in the original content.",
    "The second stage is attack simulation and finally, a signature is extracted using the decoder network stage.",
    "Thanks to the iterative learning process, the embedding is more robust against attacks applied during the second stage, and the extraction network improves the integrity of the extracted signature.",
    "The main advantage of deep learning-based watermarking over traditional watermarking is that it can be easily retrained for various applications and different attacks instead of being designed from scratch.An image or video watermarking scheme based on deep learning works as follows:1."
  ]
}